Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.22,0:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, Yorktown and Lexington - \Ntwo carrier flagships of the American Mobile Task Force
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,linked up with British-Australian Combined Fleet, \Nabout 360 nautical miles south of Guadalcanal Island, {/assembled/gathered}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,preparing for a decisive face-off with the Japanese fleet. {to meet (the enemy) and attack; to engage (the approaching enemy); to confront; to intercept}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.32,0:05:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The supreme commander \Nof the American Mobile Fleet, Admiral Fletcher {doesn't actually say rank but it'd sound weird without the rank}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.47,0:05:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,held a strategy conference \Naboard aircraft carrier Yorktown.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Intelligence says{/there are reasons to believe}, \Nthe Japanese forces, aiming to land at Port Moresby {lit is "... capturing forces/troops" but idk what he means, would assume landing party}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are expected to pass through \Nthe Solomon Sea on 7th or 8th.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.69,0:05:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what about the Japanese Mobile Fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.54,0:05:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is beyond doubt that they are moving southwards, \Nwest of the Solomon islands. {no clue what's gun here before "island"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.95,0:05:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there's still no exact data \Nof their current position.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.12,0:05:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, this is about \Nwho discovers the enemy carrier first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.41,0:05:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if just a minute or second faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.39,0:06:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In a carrier battle, even a single moment matters. {Lit: "A battle between carriers is decided by a single moment's difference."}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.08,0:06:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the Japanese and the American fleets \Nwanted to seize the initiative. {lit: were supposed to launch a preemptive/early attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.40,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hence both were combing through the area like mad. {/desperately looking for one another}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.87,0:06:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Two next days - the 5th and the 6th of May, \Nwere entirely uneventful. {/nothing happened}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.39,0:06:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, the enemy is hoping \Nto strike at our landing party tomorrow, {again, this "capture forces"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.89,0:06:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as we would be passing through Solomon Sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.35,0:06:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No, more likely... The day after tomorrow, \Nin the Coral Sea, as we would turn to Port Moresby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In case they choose the day after tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.34,0:06:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow they would probably be \Noperating here on the southern side.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.24,0:06:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all like one big game of hide-and-seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.24,0:06:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the point - whoever finds the enemy first, wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.25,0:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, we need to catch the enemy by the tail \Nand deliver a decisive blow! {/destroy}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.88,0:06:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we don't find them at the estimated location?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.15,0:06:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, we would also have \Nto turn west and cross the Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.97,0:06:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, the Japanese convoys, carrying \NPort Moresby assault party, together with their escorts,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:07:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,centered around aircraft carrier Shoho \Nto protect them from anything, {added}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.00,0:07:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,were sailing south through the central part \Nof the Solomon Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.90,0:07:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Until sometime after 9 am an enemy aircraft was spotted \Nand the whole fleet was brought into full alert.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.72,0:07:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew! Man your stations! {no clue, trusting HA here}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.33,0:07:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Direction - 90 degrees! Height - 4 degrees! \NOnly one aircraft! {actually the second one is "point of the compass; cardinal direction; bearing​" but I have no clue what's the first one and obviously height can't be 90, but also height of 4 doesn't make sense either, it's effectively on the horizon. not that it matters all that much, nobody cares so could just write in whatever makes any sense; not in HA's; }
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,After it! {chase; pursuit; tracking; stalking}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the time was gradually drawing near \Nfor the first in history carrier-on-carrier {decisive }battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.36,0:07:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was shipborne!{actually he says "there's a carrier" but idk what it means, he says it like "we have a carrier" but that doesn't make sense so I assumed he just expands in the second sentence} \NThe enemy carrier should totally be near here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.02,0:07:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Make every precaution so as not to reveal us \Nto radio detection, only then search for the enemy! {lit: our side will get caught ..., be careful enough when ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.92,0:07:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from Shokaku's recon aircraft! {sister ship of zuikaku}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.37,0:08:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Discovered enemy aircraft carrier! \N400 nautical miles southwest of Tulagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.69,0:08:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Carrier fighters{carrier-borne attack aircraft​ - hope it means fighter}, carrier bombers{trusting HA, no clue what's this kanbaku}, \Nall aircraft take off!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.63,0:08:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy fleet!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.74,0:08:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At the Japanese camp on Rabaul...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.74,0:08:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is to 170 degrees from Rossel Island, \N82 nautical miles away. {actually not "from" and not "away" but idk what else he can mean by "170 degrees of rossel"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.83,0:08:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We have concluded \Nthat the enemy split his task force in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.33,0:08:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we should attack the enemy \Nin the direction of Rossel Island with all our might.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.40,0:08:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, escorted by our mobile fleet, \Nthe convoy evacuates to the northwest.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.48,0:09:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the 5th Carrier Division has been \N400 nautical miles southwest of Tulagi for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.15,0:09:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They had already commenced \Nan all-out attack on the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.77,0:09:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.57,0:09:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a refueling ship!{tanker; military refueling vessel}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.89,0:10:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the damn carriers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.14,0:10:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Carriers!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Around this time, on the Japanese side,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.94,0:10:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,tasked with escorting a transport convoy, carrier Shoho
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.93,0:10:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was already{could be "also"} under heavy attack \Nfrom carrier-based aircraft of the American mobile fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.18,0:11:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain! A fire broke out! {no clue what's this kaji, must be fire but then it's "fire is done/been hit" and i'd expect there to be a ship name, but there's no carrier with similar name at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:World_War_II_aircraft_carriers_of_Japan; was "She was attacked." in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.41,0:11:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.32,0:11:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.17,0:12:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The loss of the aircraft carrier Shoho \Nis on us, the 5th Carrier Division! {/is the responsiblity ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.17,0:12:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistaking a tanker for a carrier \Nis a display of utter incompetence! {no clue what's this last word, was "how could you ..." in HA}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.81,0:12:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, it's taking everyone pretty long! {no clue what he means by "everyone's late"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.52,0:12:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Communications department, \Nwhat are you waiting for?! {/doing}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.13,0:12:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them to{no clue why'd he say it to communications staff so addded; maybe previous line is not comm. staff after all} return home immediately \Nafter dropping the payload! {/dropping your bombs and torpedoes, repatriate at once}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.92,0:12:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll never make it in time \Nif we keep dawdling!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.90,0:12:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Make arrangement for the returning attack vehicles \Nto be swiftly housed!{/received/accepted}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.18,0:12:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We need our entire mobile fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.89,0:12:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to and chase the enemy to the northwest \Nand smash them at full speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.68,0:13:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be sure to avenge Shoho tenfold! {to avenge (someone) by striking down their killer}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, we have obviously \Nwasted too much time already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.24,0:13:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.73,0:13:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,A night attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.25,0:13:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That one is dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.81,0:13:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Our 5th Carrier Division has brilliant pilots. {/excellent}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.11,0:13:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese commander's worries \Nwere not entirely unjustified.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.17,0:13:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The 5th Carrier Division
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.78,0:13:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,was formed immediately prior \Nto the outbreak of the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.72,0:13:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The training that pilots received was severely insufficient, \Nrendering night attack in particular a fool's errand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.08,0:14:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the 5th Carrier Division commander, \NRear Admiral Hara coerced everyone into it forcibly. {to overcome (opposition); to push past; to force one's way ... overbearing; coercive; pushy; forcible; high-handed}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.76,0:14:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do it if we're resolute enough. {lit: we can do it if with readiness to die; (in the) face of death}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.28,0:14:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. If that's what you believe in as a commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.85,0:14:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Order:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.39,0:14:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The main force
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.77,0:14:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,would perform a night attack against the enemy mobile fleet \Nthat showed up in the northern part of Coral Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Using our fleet's brilliant pilots, {actually "this ship's"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.92,0:14:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll organize the groups of 6 carrier-based bombers \Nand 9 carrier-based fighters per ship. {really unsure about this "each/per" part, maybe it's something else and he means this group is for entire fleet and prev. line was really "this ship's"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.26,0:14:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Take off as soon as the preparations are finished. \NAttack with full resolve. {lit: make attack prepared to die but that'd only kill cps so using same word as before}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.79,0:15:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese planes \Nare yet to catch any glimpse of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.38,0:15:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, our mobile fleet is sailing \Nunder the protection of the goddess of victory. {/... is smiling at ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.17,0:15:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sortie immediately! {/Attack}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a squall below. {was "to the north" in HA's, I wonder...} \NNot much we can do now! {I think he means "there's a strong wind below, therefore we can't descend and return to ship"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain! Above to the right, enemy planes! {/Upper right sky}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.19,0:15:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.19,0:15:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.56,0:15:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How did they manage to find us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All planes! Drop the torpedoes! {unsure about first word, may be "tekiki" and not "zenki"; I think he means "lose the torpedoes for better maneuverability"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.97,0:15:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as all our fighters are away, \Nthey're having a free rein! {I hope he means this - we've no fighters, they're taking it easy, but idk why'd they have no fighters since we know the groups included more fighters than bombers}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.15,0:16:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for that carrier! Carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.38,0:16:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's gotta be a carrier nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.93,0:16:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.21,0:16:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,5th Carrier Division reports!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.86,0:16:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Still unable to discover the enemy. \NReceiving heavy fire from enemy fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.49,0:16:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to engage enemy fighters. {lit: in the middle of battle with}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.74,0:16:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Close to annihilation. {actually "our unit is annihilated" but that'd contradict the previous lines - why'd he say it in the end and not the beginning of a report?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it all. Any idea which way our hometown is? {he says "where did my house/home go" - either he means their carrier from which they took off, or it's some obscure japanese phrase for being homesick (unlikely), but if he means carrier it's gotta be a joke, even if he doesnt look or sound jokingly at all, because there are obviously no bathtubs on a carrier, so maybe "wagaya" is a military slang for carrier but he plays around it, pretending he means his real home and that's the joke? either way, very hard line to wrap around}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather go home now and jump in a hot bath. {/I want to go home and take a bath}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.31,0:16:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.12,0:16:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at this rate, we can only hope for one, \Nnonsensically giant bath. {lit: ridiculous/stupidly big}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.20,0:16:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, and what's worse, it's ice-cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.15,0:16:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.20,0:16:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,60 degrees to the right, locating friendly carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.74,0:16:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.37,0:16:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! I see, I see. {/there it is}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.93,0:16:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Deploy landing gear at once! {lit: enter the landing on an aircraft carrier; deck-landing order; system; structure; set-up; organization/mode - not sure what is implied by that on such an ancient plane or how to make it clear in english}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.38,0:17:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.49,0:17:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an enemy carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.51,0:17:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The markings{lit: digits/figures - would assume he means letters} on the deck \Nand the bridge shape are not right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.62,0:17:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.78,0:17:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the enemy! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.03,0:17:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They're finally back! {/seem to return}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sirs,{we also called him captain of the plane, but this one is captain of the ship so idk, would go for something unrelated} enemy carrier in the immediate vicinity! {lit: right there/close that way}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.03,0:18:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure? {Is it true?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Other vehicles also saw it clearly. {he doesn't exactly say "also" but w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.96,0:18:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.75,0:18:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Night-time attacks are demanding. {/difficult}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.57,0:18:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be helped now. \NHow about tomorrow? {trusting HA here, tho this doesn't sound like myonichi}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of the Coral Sea entered its second day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Too impatient to wait for the dawn, \Nboth Japan and the US
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.30,0:18:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,dispatched their reconnaissance aircraft \Nin search of one another's carrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.26,0:18:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The enemy carrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.04,0:18:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there's a carrier! {/looks like they've a carrier [in this task force]}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.51,0:18:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{Carrier }Shokaku's reconnaissance aircraft reports:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Observing enemy carrier. \NWill maintain visual contact. {/stay in touch/follow/shadow}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:18:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Position in relation to us - 205 degrees. Distance{added} - \N235 nautical miles. Course 170 degrees. Speed 16 knots
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H9C5FBD&\blur0.7\bord1\fs30\3c&H050104&\frz305.4\pos(428.18,265.62)}Japanese Fleet
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz308.8\c&HD8D6EE&\blur0.7\bord1\fs30\3c&H050104&\pos(368.74,-35.16)}Solomon Islands
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEEF2FA&\blur0.7\bord1\fs50\3c&H050104&\pos(407.7,698.93)\frz358.5}Coral Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEEF2FA&\blur0.7\bord1\fs50\3c&H050104&\frz357.8\pos(-1.15,30.86)}Solomon Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz307.9\c&HEEF2FA&\blur0.7\bord1\fs30\3c&H050104&\pos(1020.83,402.51)}Guadalcanal Island
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HEEF2FA&\blur0.7\bord1\fs30\3c&H050104&\frz356.1\pos(1103.38,182.13)}Tulagi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.94,0:19:01.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\frz303.4\c&H73C2DB&\blur0.7\bord1\fs30\3c&H050104&\pos(726.01,704)}Combined ABDACOM{/assembled allied/united} Fleet \N(US / Britain / Australia)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.37,0:19:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Carriers - 2, battleship - 1. \NHeavy cruisers - 2, light cruiser - 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.19,0:19:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus six destroyers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.45,0:19:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, we now have barely enough fuel for the return trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.55,0:19:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We made a sufficiently detailed report, \Nso it should be fine{ to return}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.68,0:19:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.90,0:19:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm breaking visual contact with the enemy \Nand returning us home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.19,0:19:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At almost the exact same time, American reconnaissance \Naircraft also discovered the Japanese mobile fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.21,0:20:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather is turning volatile. {/prone to changing rapidly}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.19,0:20:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best that we show our allies the exact way. {/precisely}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Reconnaissance aircraft reports:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.65,0:20:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Canceling our return. \NWill guide our attack squadron instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.67,0:20:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Will guide our attack squadron instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.57,0:20:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest is up to you, attack squadron!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.55,0:20:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, our fuel is no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.34,0:21:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Squadron, proceed to attack! {trusting HA's Everyone, charge!, no clue what's first word}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.39,0:21:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.43,0:21:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Full starboard! {trusting HA, not important}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.66,0:21:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.18,0:21:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, this storm must be a God's providence. {divine wind (esp. a typhoon thought to have protected Japan from a Mongolian invasion in the 13th century)}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.46,0:21:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, Shokaku is not depending on anyone else \Nto stand out against the enemy. {hope he means this - to take on; to undertake; to accept; to take charge of; to assume responsibility for single-handedly; alone; single-handed}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.68,0:22:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They sure did quite a number on us. {/is severely damaged/done - no clue how is this related to zuikaku's appearance}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.20,0:22:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.62,0:22:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as the battle is over, \Ncarrier Zuikaku appears on the scene. {presence; appearance; attendance; visit; going out}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.98,0:22:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Communications department!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.63,0:22:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Report to Rabaul for Fleet Commander:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.67,0:22:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack unit returned at around 11 am \Nand was housed. {no clue what's this junji, was "The attacking force is returning around 11 am," in HA's; added last part for better readability}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.26,0:22:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently consolidating what's left of our forces, \Nbut no prospect for re-attack today. {/second wave}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.28,0:22:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, the exhaustion \Nof both the offensive ability and the fuel supplies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.18,0:22:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,renders the nighttime high-speed navigation too risky. {lit: at night, we can't cruise at high speed - no clue why only at night or what's it have to do with exhaustion}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.62,0:22:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who received the report \Nwas the Commander-in-Chief of the 4th fleet, Inoue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.71,0:22:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing we can do about it, \Nif even Shokaku came under attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.78,0:22:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Order them to hold the attack and head north.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.18,0:22:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Moresby Offensive is postponed! {/Port Moresby Operation }
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.18,0:22:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What? They postponed the Port Moresby Operation?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.69,0:23:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's order them to pursue the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon receiving the {pursuit }order \Nfrom the Combined Fleet Commander-in-Chief Yamamoto,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the 4th Fleet Mobile Task Force headed south \Nat full speed when it was 2:00 am on the 9th.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.87,0:23:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, they never managed \Nto catch up with the American task force.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.18,0:23:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately upon hearing this report, \NCommander-in-Chief Yamamoto
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.19,0:23:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,rearranged the 4th Fleet, \Nappointing its Mobile Task Force elsewhere. {/took away from ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.53,0:23:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason was because the day was drawing near \Nfor Operation Midway, planned next, to take place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.21,0:23:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.32,0:23:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,he was dissatisfied with his commander, \Nwho was constantly letting the victory slip away. {lit: close run; just falling short of success of endgame (esp. in shogi or used figuratively)/checkmate - I think he means "was one step away from winning decisively but didn't manage it in the end"; can't say for sure, was it yamamoto disappointed with the Inoue commander, or was it Inoue disappointed himself with how things turned up. After all, we're seeing Inoue gnawing his nails}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.73,0:23:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Damage-wise, both the Japanese and US sides \Nsuffered approximately the same losses in this battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.02,0:23:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get overly concerned \Nwith your allies' safety, {lit: when too caught up in ... damage/losses}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.96,0:23:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you overlook the importance of damaging the enemy{ as well}, \Nand let the operation deteriorate into a stalemate. {I hope he means this by "enemy's damage gets overlooked/missed/let pass, and the operations stalls/comes to stagnation"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.07,0:23:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, the 4th Fleet of the IJN emerged victorious \Ntactics-wise, but got beaten strategy-wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.25,0:24:07.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(100,0)}The Pacific War taught us the preciousness of peace.\NBut also instilled numerous lessons on how to live.{太平洋戦争はわれわれに平和の尊さを教えたがまた生きるための教訓を数多くのこしている}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.57,0:24:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason for which the war on the Pacific was let loose \Nwas the acquisition of the oil-rich southern regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.21,0:24:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In the invasion of Java Island, {actually "operation of capturing Java Island"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.12,0:24:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan sent ahead three forward battalions, \Ntasked with securing the targeted oil fields. {not a cluewhat's this rakka, maybe "fall; drop; descent; coming down" like in "disembarked"?; maybe proper name, will fix if made clear in next ep.}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.33,0:24:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander was hoping to thus negate \Nthe possibility of the enemy sabotaging it. {as much as possible}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.46,0:24:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Indonesian National Independence Movement
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.13,0:24:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,also took advantage of Japan's invasion. {lit: made japanese side operation advantageous - idk, maybe it means they helped the japanese}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.25,0:24:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss the next week's decision: \NThe Fall of Java. {ジャワ攻略}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.61,0:24:38.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 9\NThe Fall of Java
Comment: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{ch}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.80,0:24:48.43,Default,,0,0,50,,If you're a man, let's put your strength to test{男だったら　力を試せ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.43,0:24:52.72,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, keep your hopes sizzling{男だったら　希望(のぞみ)を燃やせ}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.75,0:24:57.11,Default,,0,0,50,,If you are a man, don't lose your heart{男だったら　くじけるな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.11,0:25:05.68,Default,,0,0,50,,Because there's just you and me, a man and a man{俺もおまえも　男と男}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.68,0:25:14.51,Default,,0,0,50,,With crimson blood flowing in our veins all the same{おなじ真赤な　血が通う}
